oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Commencement exercises for Fisk High School
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Program of commencement exercises for Fisk High School, which took place at the Fisk Memorial Chapel in Nashville, Tennessee. Class Roll includes six graduates.

The Fisk Memorial Chapel is an ecumencial, non-denominational, and interdenominational church that was constructed in 1892. The Chapel is a primary assembly area on campus for Fisk University sponsoring numerous public functions including concerts, lectures, conferences, and graduation exercises, etc. Included among those who have visited the Chapel are Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., Booker T. Washington, Louis Armstrong, Jesse Jackson, Merle Haggard, etc. as well as being home to the Fisk Jubilee Singers.
